  "id": "phekb-peanut-allergy-dx",
  "source": "phekb",
  "source_id": "peanut-allergy",
  "name": "Peanut Allergy - Diagnosis Code Query (Pediatric, Ages 1-17)",
  "description": "Tests ability to find peanut allergy patients via diagnosis code with pediatric age restriction (1-17). Second pediatric phenotype (after SECO). Reuses PatientFilters schema with chained patient.birthdate filter.",
  "prompt": "Find pediatric patients (ages 1-17) with a documented peanut allergy.",
  "prompts": {
    "naive": "Find kids with peanut allergy.",
    "broad": "Find pediatric patients (ages 1 through 17) with a documented diagnosis of peanut allergy.",
    "expert": "I need to find pediatric patients with a documented peanut allergy diagnosis, restricting the cohort to children between one and seventeen years of age. Search Condition resources for the SNOMED CT code representing allergy to peanut. Because FHIR R4 does not expose a direct patient age parameter, the age restriction must be implemented as a chained filter on the patient's birthdate — computing the date range that corresponds to ages one through seventeen relative to the current reference date and applying both a lower and upper bound on the birthdate field."
  },
